Only cost me a dollar.</i>

16
00:00:43,347 --> 00:00:45,349
Is one of the tips
"make a crappy newsletter

17
00:00:45,393 --> 00:00:47,177
and charge idiots
a dollar for it"?

18
00:00:48,222 --> 00:00:50,006
No, but not a bad idea.

19
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,879
Listen to this: "Raise bees
and sell the honey for profit."

20
00:00:53,923 --> 00:00:55,794
Do it, and I'm living
with Meemaw.

21
00:00:55,838 --> 00:00:58,188
"Sell blood
or non-vital organs."

22
00:00:58,232 --> 00:01:00,060
<i>Mm, give 'em your brain.
You're not using it.</i>

23
00:01:00,103 --> 00:01:02,323
(LAUGHS)

24
00:01:02,366 --> 00:01:05,065
I think that's the only time
I've ever heard you laugh.

25
00:01:05,108 --> 00:01:07,284
That's the only time
you've ever been funny.

26
00:01:07,328 --> 00:01:11,767
Oh, platinum can be extracted
from ordinary roadside gravel.

27
00:01:11,810 --> 00:01:12,942
No, it can't.

28
00:01:12,985 --> 00:01:14,074
Actually, it can.

29
00:01:14,117 --> 00:01:15,988
Catalytic converters
contain platinum.

30
00:01:16,032 --> 00:01:17,599
Microparticles of that platinum

31
00:01:17,642 --> 00:01:18,730
are expelled in the exhaust

32
00:01:18,774 --> 00:01:20,471
and are mixed in
with the gravel.

33
00:01:20,515 --> 00:01:23,344
See? This thing's a gold mine.

34
00:01:23,387 --> 00:01:27,348
It would be more apt
to call it a platinum mine.

35
00:01:28,523 --> 00:01:30,481
I laughed at your joke.

36
00:01:30,525 --> 00:01:33,397
<i>♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪</i>

37
00:01:33,441 --> 00:01:36,183
<i>♪ Yesterday I moved a mountain</i>

38
